---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 6
  Paragraph: 13
Title: The Great And Venerable Teacher
---
The Great Clod burdens me with form, labors me with life, eases me in
old age, and rests me in death. So if I think well of my life, for the
same reason I must think well of my death.
